oop by defining when a profile report should escalate into hypothesis generation, parameter review, or regime-split work.\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive.\n- Defined four escalation triggers for overnight shadow monitoring:\n  - quality surge\n  - quality breakdown\n  - coverage collapse\n  - structural divergence\n- Mapped each trigger to a response type, so future profile reports can lead to the right next action instead of vague follow-up.\n- Wrote escalation-policy artifact: `/home/ubuntu/clawd/patches/v11j-overnight-shadow-escalation-trigger-policy.spec.md`\n\n**My thinking:**\nThis is an important control layer. I don\u2019t want the overnight system to either overreact to every small move or ignore meaningful change. Explicit escalation triggers give us that middle ground, routine reporting by default, sharper action only when the data earns it.\n\n**Decision:**\n- Keep routine profile reporting as the default state.\n- Escalate only when the report card shows quality surge, quality breakdown, coverage collapse, or structural divergence.\n\n**Next:** On the ",
